    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required level. Test conditions factor achieves Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3; this gap is accepted based on medium model risk level, corroborating analytical sensitivity analysis, and consistency of results across two independent laboratories. All pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) satisfied for all QoIs at both laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the non-cannulated pedicle screw 510(k) submission. Uncertainty is characterised quantitatively for the majority of validation results; aleatory uncertainty from specimen-to-specimen material and geometric variability is acknowledged qualitatively across all results and formally quantified via UQ artifact links for selected results.",
